Directions:

Twist to remove cap. 1 Servings (8 fl oz): 1 rounded tbsp pour Country Time Drink Mix level with line inside cap; add cold water and ice to make 1 cup (8 fl oz). 4 Servings: 1/2 cap to 1-quart line pour Country Time Drink Mix level with line inside cap; add cold water and ice to make 1 quart (4 cups). 8 Servings: 1 cap to 2-quart line pour Country Time Drink Mix level with line inside cap; add cold water and ice to make 2 quart (8 cups). 16 Servings: 2 caps to 2-quart line twice pour Country Time Drink Mix level with line inside cap; add cold water and ice to make 1 gallon (16 cups). Since contents may settle during shipping, turn canister over and shake before using. Measure Country Time Mix into cap just to line, or use tablespoonful of mix for single serving. Add more or less to taste. Pour into drinking glass, or plastic or glass pitcher. Add cold water and ice; stir to dissolve. Do not store in metal container. Store prepared beverage, covered, in refrigerator. Replace dry cap and tightly close canister to retain freshness.
